observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to: 

Direct the Municipal Accountant to close the PPE and other related accounts pertaining to the semi-expendable properties previously classified as PPE;

Require the Municipal Accountant to verify the CIP account and make the necessary adjustments in the books;

Create an Inventory Committee to conduct physical count of all PPE accounts of the Municipality;

Direct the Inventory Committee to prepare the RPCPPE upon completion of the physical inventory; and

Require the GSO and Municipal Accountant to ensure that all PPE included in the RPCPPE are duly recorded in the PCs and the PPELCs.

We also recommended that the Municipality avail of the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with reliable PPE balances presented in the financial statements.

We recommended and it was agreed that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the Municipal Accountant to do the following:
Establish Subsidiary Ledgers for the Disaster Response and Rescue Equipment and, with the assistance of the MDRRM Officer, classify the existing DRR equipment according to its purpose;
Draw the necessary adjusting entries to record the adjustments relative to the erroneous capitalization of the repair and maintenance in the current and prior years, if applicable;
Record the transactions in their appropriate accounts in its subsequent financial transactions in order to achieve accurate financial reporting; and
If practicable, determine the amount recorded as Special Trust Fund in the Calendar Year 2024 which should have been reverted back to the unappropriated surplus of the General Fund.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to direct the Municipal Accountant and other concerned personnel to:

a. Exert effort in retrieving data and information by coordinating with the source agencies concerned;

b. Conduct reconciliation of the Due to NGA’s account with available records and make proper adjustments for deficiencies noted; 

c. Coordinate with the Municipal Treasurer for the refund of the unutilized balances to the source agencies; and

d. Make proper adjustments for unexpended balances of the LGU counterpart in specific projects; and

Henceforth, maintain subsidiary ledgers for each fund received from NGAs and monitor closely the transactions pertaining thereto.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to: 

Direct the Supply Officer to prepare and submit the SSMI supported with the RIS to the Municipal Accountant as basis in preparing the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to record the supplies and materials issued; 

Create an Inventory Committee to conduct a physical count of all inventories of the Municipality and prepare the RPCI in accordance with the prescribed format; 

Require the Municipal Accountant and the Supply Officer to reconcile their records based on the results of the physical inventory;

Henceforth, require the Inventory Committee to conduct semesterly the physical count of inventories and prepare the RPCI; and

Submit to the Auditor the RCPI not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to: 

Create an Inventory Committee to conduct physical count of all PPE accounts of the Municipality;


Direct the Inventory Committee to complete the physical inventory-taking and prepare the RPCPPE;


Instruct the Property Officer and Municipal Accountant to ensure that all PPEs included in the RPCPPE are duly recorded in the Property Cards (PCs) maintained by the General Services Office and the PPELCs maintained by the Accounting Unit; and

Avail the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to come up with reliable PPE balances presented in the financial statements.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to: 

Direct the Supply Officer to prepare and submit the SSMI supported with the RIS to the Municipal Accountant as basis in preparing the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to record the supplies and materials issued; 

Create an Inventory Committee to conduct a physical count of all inventories of the Municipality and prepare the RPCI in accordance with the prescribed format; 

