We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) require the:
Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator to submit a revised project proposal categorically including financial assistance to barangay officials and other barangay volunteers duly approved by the Governor of the Province of Iloilo as per MOA dated March 16, 2020, for the transfer of funds in the total amount of ₱5.918 million; and

Municipal Accountant to submit the supporting documents for payment of financial assistance to tricycle/trisikad drivers totaling ₱1.004 million as follows:

LTO driver's license of recipients which contain the personal identification of drivers as no other identification could be found in the payroll;

Certificate of residency issued by Punong Barangays where the drivers reside to prove that they are residents of the Municipality;

Certificate of indigency issued by the MSWDO;

Certificate of non-availment of financial assistance from other government agency issued by the concerned driver.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive: 
Adhere to the rules and regulations on accounting and reporting of donations per COA Circular No. 2020-009. Henceforth, instruct the MDRRMO to submit the required Summary/List of Donations Received, Distributed and Balances together with the supporting documents such as the acknowledgement receipts for in-kind donations, official receipts for cash donations and inventory list of the undistributed items or goods;

Instruct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to issue Official Receipts on all cash donations received and maintain a separate bank account with an authorized government depository bank; 

Delegate to the Acting General Services Officer the receiving of in-kind donations and the inventory and monitoring thereof; and

Direct the Municipal Accountant to record in the books all in-kind donations and the cash donations under the Trust Liabilities-DRRMF account per Section B.4 of COA Circular No. 2014-002.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) adhere with the rules and regulations in the disbursement of COVID-19 funds pursuant to the above-cited rules and regulations and require the:
Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking supporting documents as follows: 

Executive Order issued showing personnel were authorized to report for work during the period of implementation of Enhanced Community Quarantine (ECQ) and Daily Time Record indicating the number of days that concerned personnel physically reported during the specified period of ECQ per Section 4.3 and 4.5 of DBM Budget Circular No. 2020-1; 

Billing statements and delivery receipts on daily basis for catering services for front liners, repatriated OFWs and LSIs; Attendance sheets duly signed by front liners whose names are indicated therein and by the MHO personnel in-charge of quarantine facilities;

Driver’s Trip Tickets properly filled-up as to name of passengers, signature and certification of passengers that the service vehicles were used for official use and for COVID-19 related PPAs only pursuant to Section 2.1.6 of DILG-DBM JMC No. 01;

List of occupants be attached to justify for the high cost of bill every month and also, the meter readings validated by a municipal employee;

Pictures of work done and inspection report for labor payroll for the construction of quarantine facilities; and

Funeral service contracts and billing statements from the funeral parlor for payment of cremation.

MDRRMO to submit the activity design for Libre Sakay Program, contract of service made by and between the Municipality and the Operators of Public Utility Jeepneys stating the specific period within which the Operator will provide the required services, as well as the health protocols to be observed and Certificate of Public Convenience pursuant to Section 3.1 of GPPB Circular No. 2020-01; 
BAC Chairman to submit the Omnibus Sworn Statements (OSS) issued by vendors in the prescribed form required by Section 3.4 of GPPB Circular No. 2020-01 and notice of award  issued to the vendors as required for emergency procurement on emergency cases; Justification for various purchase orders issued to the same Suppliers in different dates covered by only one purchase request considering that other Suppliers are available in the locality selling the same items pursuant to Section 3.1 of GPPB Circular No. 01-2020;

Municipal Health Officer to submit the Daily Time Record (DTRs) indicating the number of days that concerned personnel physically reported during the specified period and accomplishment reports of personnel granted with hazard pay indicating exposure to hazard in specific areas and circumstances approved by MHO pursuant to Section 3.2 of DBM and DOH Joint Circular No. 2016-1; and

OIC-Municipal Social Welfare Development Officer to submit the DTRs indicating the number of days that concerned personnel physically reported during the specified period and accomplishment reports signed by LCE, as well as, established procedure of management in the determination of personnel entitled to hazard pay exposed to great danger, occupational risks, perils to life and physical hardships and only during actual periods of actual exposure to hazards and hardships pursuant to Section 5.1 and 5.2 of DBM and DSWD Joint Circular No. 1, series of 2018.

Henceforth, the concerned personnel see to it that all disbursements are duly supported with complete documentation to ensure the propriety, validity and legality of transactions and to avoid suspension of disbursements in audit.
